premise_source_doc_sentence: Advantages of cluster randomised controlled trials over individually randomised controlled trials include the ability to study interventions that can not be directed toward selected individuals  (  e.g. , a radio show about lifestyle changes  )  and the ability to control for `` contamination '' across individuals  (  e.g. , one individual 's changing behaviors may influence another individual to do so  )  .
